    <name>
				<text>13.5.2.2 Definite integrals</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Evaluate the following.</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>\({\displaystyle\int_{@l1@}^{@u1@} {@exp1@}\ \mathrm{d}x} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] (give an exact value) [[feedback:prt1]]</li>

    <li>\({\displaystyle\int_{@l2@}^{@u2@} {@exp2@}\ \mathrm{d}t} =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] (round to \(4\) decimal places) [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">

    <li>
        <p>We need to calculate the integral \( I =\int {@exp1@}\ \mathrm{d}x .\)</p>
        <p>Using \( u = {@uu@}\) we get \(\dfrac{du}{dx} = {@du@} \Rightarrow \ \mathrm{d}x = \frac{1}{{@du@}}\ \mathrm{d}u.\)</p>
        <p>\[ \begin{aligned} I = \int {@exp1@}\ \mathrm{d}x = \int u^{{@po@}}\ \mathrm{d}x &amp;= \int u^{{@po@}} \frac{1}{{@du@}}\ \mathrm{d}u, \\ &amp;= \int e^u \ \mathrm{d}u, \\ &amp;= {@I1@}. \end{aligned}\]</p>
        <p>So \(\displaystyle{\int_{@l1@}^{@u1@} {@exp1@}\ \mathrm{d}x = \left[ {@I1@} \right]_{@l1@}^{@u1@} = {@ta1@}}.\)</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>We need to calculate the integral \( I =\int {@exp2@}\ \mathrm{d}t .\)</p>
        <p>Using \(u = {@vv@}\) we get \(\dfrac{\mathrm{d}u}{\mathrm{d}t} = {@dv@} \Rightarrow \ \mathrm{d}t = \frac{1}{{@dv@}}\ \mathrm{d}u.\)</p>
        <p>\(\displaystyle{ I = \int {@exp2@}\ \mathrm{d}t = \int {@p1@} e^{u} \, \mathrm{d}t = \int {@p1@} e^u \frac{1}{{@dv@}}\ \mathrm{d}u= {@I2@}}.\)</p>
        <p>So \(\displaystyle{ \int_{@l2@}^{@u2@} {@exp1@}\ \mathrm{d}t = \left[ {@I2@} \right]_{@l2@}^{@u2@}= {@ta2@}}.\) </p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
